# **Treatment Director**

## **Position Overview**

The Treatment Director is a full-time, exempt position reporting directly to the CEO **[T3C] and/or Program Director**. This role is responsible for the primary oversight and clinical management of the agency's therapeutic services, ensuring that all treatment programs are effectively directed and managed **[T3C] in accordance with the agency's Evidence-informed Treatment Model and Service Package requirements**.

**[T3C]** This position fulfills the Treatment Director requirements for all T3C Service Packages including Mental & Behavioral Health Support Services, IDD/Autism Spectrum Disorder Support Services, Substance Use Support Services, Short-Term Assessment Support Services, and T3C Treatment Foster Family Care Support Services.

## **Primary Objectives**

* Provide leadership and overall management of the treatment program  
* Ensure the delivery of high-quality therapeutic services to children with emotional disorders, intellectual disabilities, autism spectrum disorder, and other special needs  
* Facilitate a trauma-informed care environment that supports the unique needs of each child  
* **\[T3C\]** Supervise all clinical staff providing services under specific Service Packages  
* **\[T3C\]** Ensure compliance with T3C Service Package treatment requirements  
* **\[TBRI\]** Promote Trust-Based Relational Intervention practices throughout clinical services

## **Key Responsibilities**

**Clinical Oversight**

* Monitor the progress of children in collaboration with the Administrator and Program Director  
* Supervise the development of Master Plans, Quarterly Reviews, and service plan addendums for children in foster care  
* **\[T3C\]** Provide supervision to Service Package specific therapists including:  
  * Licensed Therapists for mental health services  
  * **\[T3C\]** Licensed Chemical Dependency Counselors (LCDC) for substance use services  
  * **\[T3C\]** Qualified Credentialed Counselors (QCC) for substance use services  
  * **\[T3C\]** Licensed Sex Offender Treatment Providers (LSOTP) for sexual aggression services  
* **\[T3C\]** Ensure treatment aligns with desired individual outcomes for each Service Package
* **\[T3C\]** Ensure On-Call Licensed Therapist coverage for Treatment Foster Family Care (24/7)
* **\[T3C\]** Provide clinical oversight for substance use treatment coordination
* **\[T3C\]** Review Short-Term Assessment recommendations before Service Package determination

**Program Management**

* **\[T3C\]** Oversee implementation of the agency's Evidence-informed Treatment Model  
* **\[T3C\]** Ensure treatment services meet specific Service Package expectations  
* Participate in weekly clinical and administrative meetings  
* Represent Refuge House to the public and referral agencies  
* **\[T3C\]** Collaborate with Behavior Support Specialists/Mentors on treatment planning

**Quality Assurance and Compliance**

* Review and approve incident reports  
* Inform licensing representatives of incidents as required and participate in internal investigations  
* Prepare children's files, family files, training records, and other documentation for quality assurance purposes  
* Contribute to Performance Quality Improvement (PQI) initiatives  
* **\[T3C\]** Support the Continuous Quality Assurance and Improvement Program  
* **\[T3C\]** Monitor treatment fidelity to Evidence-informed Treatment Model

**Staff Development**

* **\[T3C\]** Ensure all clinical staff are trained in the agency's Treatment Model  
* **\[TBRI\]** Provide TBRI consultation to clinical team  
* Provide consultation, training, and technical assistance to caregivers regarding trauma-informed caregiving techniques  
* **\[T3C\]** Coordinate with Staff Training and Workforce Development on clinical training needs

**Additional Responsibilities**

* Be available on-call for supervisory issues  
* Maintain knowledge of and compliance with Refuge House policies, procedures, and licensing requirements  
* **\[T3C\]** Participate in Service Package credentialing processes
* **\[T3C\]** Ensure clinical documentation meets Service Package requirements

**Service Package Clinical Oversight**

*Substance Use Support Services Oversight:*

* Review and approve substance use assessment recommendations
* Consult on relapse response and treatment plan adjustments
* Coordinate with substance use treatment providers
* Ensure non-punitive approach maintained across treatment team
* Provide clinical guidance for MAT coordination when applicable
* Review drug screening results in clinical context
* **Cross-Reference:** FC-SU-01

*Short-Term Assessment Support Services Oversight:*

* Approve assessment plans and methodology
* Review assessment findings and Service Package recommendations
* Provide clinical consultation for emerging concerns during assessment
* Ensure assessment documentation supports package determination
* **Cross-Reference:** FC-STASS-01

*T3C Treatment Foster Family Care Oversight:*

* **\[CRITICAL\]** Provide or coordinate On-Call Licensed Therapist availability (24/7 requirement per T3C Blueprint p.138)
* **\[CRITICAL\]** Conduct 60-day Continued Stay Reviews jointly with Program Director
* **\[CRITICAL\]** Provide written confirmation of continued appropriateness within 15 business days
* Supervise Licensed Therapists providing intensive therapy (1:11 ratio)
* Oversee step-down planning and readiness assessment
* Review crisis patterns and treatment implications
* Coordinate psychiatric services and medication management
* Ensure treatment intensity matches high-acuity population needs
* Monitor 365-day maximum length of service compliance
* **Cross-Reference:** FC-TFFC-01; FC-CSR-01

## **Qualifications**

**Required Education and Experience \- Standard Services**

* Must be a psychiatrist or psychologist; OR  
* Hold a Master's degree in a human services field from an accredited college or university with three years of experience providing treatment services for children with emotional disorders, including one year in a residential setting; OR  
* Be a licensed master social worker, licensed clinical social worker, licensed professional counselor, or licensed marriage and family therapist with three years of similar experience

**\[T3C\] Additional Qualifications for IDD/Autism Spectrum Disorder Services** If overseeing IDD/Autism services, may alternatively be:

* **\[T3C\]** A registered nurse; OR  
* **\[T3C\]** Certified by the Texas Education Agency as an education diagnostician with a master's degree in special education or human services field, and have three years of experience working with children with intellectual disabilities or autism spectrum disorder

**Required Knowledge and Skills**

* Experience working with children with intellectual disabilities or autism spectrum disorder is preferred  
* Strong ability to handle cultural differences within the service population and staff  
* Excellent communication, organizational, writing, and relationship development skills  
* Ability to respond calmly to emergencies and de-escalate tense situations  
* **\[T3C\]** Knowledge of Service Package requirements and expectations
* **\[T3C\]** Understanding of Evidence-informed Treatment Models
* **\[TBRI\]** Proficiency in Trust-Based Relational Intervention approaches

**Preferred Qualifications**

* Experience with adolescent substance use treatment
* Knowledge of psychiatric emergency response
* Familiarity with step-down treatment models

## **Additional Requirements**

* **\[T3C\]** Must be an actual employee of the Child Placing Agency (this position cannot be contracted)  
* Must complete pre-service training including:  
  * **\[TBRI\]** Trust-Based Relational Intervention (TBRI) within 90 days  
  * Trauma-informed care training (one hour) within 90 days  
  * Human trafficking training (four hours) within 90 days  
  * **\[T3C\]** Agency's Evidence-informed Treatment Model training  
  * **\[T3C\]** Service Package specific clinical requirements  
* Must meet ongoing training requirements related to trauma-informed care practices  
* **\[T3C\]** Complete annual training per T3C and Minimum Standards requirements  
* Pass comprehensive background checks and drug screening  
* Maintain appropriate professional licensure  
* Available for on-call rotation as needed

**Physical Requirements**

* Ability to travel to foster homes and other locations as needed  
* Capable of sitting for extended periods for documentation  
* Mental and emotional capacity to handle secondary trauma  
* Ability to respond to crisis situations

**Working Conditions**

* Primarily office-based with occasional field visits  
* Some evening and weekend availability required  
* Exposure to emotionally challenging situations  
* Collaborative team environment

This position requires a dedicated professional who can manage complex therapeutic environments while ensuring compliance with all relevant laws and regulations. The ideal candidate will be committed to improving the quality of life for children under their care by fostering a supportive and effective treatment environment.
